parameters:
Female Student A: "I saw Saionji-san this morning, and she seemed
really angry. I wonder what happened?"

Female Student B: "Hmm, why don't you ask her directly? She's in the
next classroom, right?"
Female Student A: "No way... I'm too scared to ask."

Female Student B: "That's true. You never know what she might do to
you if you get on her bad side."
99_黒背景
\n[6]: "I'm sorry, teacher, I'm late..."
Teacher: "Amasawa, it's rare for you to be late."

Teacher: "You've been absent from school for two weeks, right? Are you
still feeling unwell?"
\n[6]: "No, I'm fine now."
Teacher: "I see..."
Teacher: "Then, take your seat quickly."
Teacher: "Now, let's resume the lesson."
Teacher: "This becomes like this..."
Teacher: "And therefore..."
Teacher: "...this is the answer."
Teacher: "Did you take proper notes? It will be on the test."

Teacher: "Lately, there haven't been any rumors of Zaidargg appearing, so
we will definitely have the test this time."

Teacher: "We're going to make up for the school days lost because of
Zaidargg!"
\n[6]: (So, Zaidargg has been quiet since then...)

\n[6]: (That man who appeared in the Urban District, it seems Yui
defeated him...)
\n[6]: (If it's peaceful now, Yui will be fine even without me...)
Karen: "...Amasawa-kun"
Karen: "...Amasawa-kun"
\n[6]: "Saionji-san?"
Karen: "Did you get to see Morisaki?"
\n[6]: "No, I didn't..."
Karen: "Wasn't she at Samejima's house?"

\n[6]: "I was able to talk to Samejima at the apartment Saionji-san
told me about, but he said Yui wasn't there..."
\n[6]: "I'm not sure if it's true or not..."
Karen: "What do you mean?"
\n[6]: "I thought I heard Yui's voice faintly through the intercom."

\n[6]: "I think there's a possibility he's lying, so I'm going to go
again today."

Karen: "Even if you go again, you'll just be brushed off like
yesterday."
\n[6]: "I know, but there's no other way."
Karen: "..."
Karen: "Can't be helped. Then, I'll go with you."
Karen: "I have the keys to that apartment, so we can get inside."
\n[6]: "Eh, but isn't that breaking and entering...?"
Karen: "You're mistaken. That apartment is my property."

Karen: "I let him live there when he was my boyfriend. And now, he's
just using it without permission."

Karen: "Besides, Sky High is an entire building owned by Saionji
Pharmaceuticals."

Karen: "Otherwise, there's no way such a guy could live in that
apartment."
Karen: "Yes, I'll open Samejima's room for you."

Karen: "I lent him all the rooms on the fifth floor. No matter which
room he's using, I have the master key so it's easy to get in."
Karen: "See for yourself whether Morisaki is really there or not."
\n[6]: "...Thank you, Saionji-san. For everything..."
Teacher: "Hey! You two over there!"
Teacher: "Saionji and Amasawa!"

Teacher: "We're in the middle of class. What are you two flirting
about!"
\n[6]: "I'm sorry..."

Karen: "Teacher! It seems like Amasawa-kun isn't feeling well, so I'll
take him to the nurse's office."
Teacher: "...Is that so. Then, I'm counting on you."
Karen: "Let's go, Amasawa-kun."
99_黒背景
